data.title: Three years ago today, we left Utah and moved to Burbank, California to work in the film industry. Much to Megan’s and my surprise, we...
data.meta_description:
819 likes, 14 comments - alanseawright on December 28, 2022: "Three years ago today, we left Utah and moved to Burbank, California to work in the film industry. 
Much to Megan’s and my surprise, we LOVED living in the LA area. It wasn’t perfect, but we made friends quickly, had a great church congregation, and come on: we wore flip-flops on New Year’s Day! 
Things were really looking up! 
2 1/2 months later a global pandemic completely shut the film industry down, I lost my job, and had no prospects. 
We came back to Utah and lived in my in-laws basement collecting unemployment checks for several months, before I was able to start doing remote editing work. 

It was one of the worst times of my life. So I started making YouTube videos with a friend of mine. 

Life is unpredictable and hard and messy and beautiful. 

I love it here in Utah, but I still want to move back to LA. Who knows what’s going to happen? Certainly not me.".
